article.description: Matt Hauser had 13 points to lead five Portland State players in double figures as the Vikings routed Puget Sound 94-69 on Tuesday night in their season opener.
article.headline: Hauser carries Portland St. past Puget Sound 94-69
article.linkText: Hauser carries Portland St. past Puget Sound 94-69
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Matt Hauser had 13 points to lead five Portland State players in double figures as the Vikings routed Puget Sound 94-69 on Tuesday night in their season opener. Holland Woods, Alonzo Walker, Sal Nuhu and Kyle Greeley added 12 points apiece for the Vikings. Woods also had five assists and five steals for the Vikings, while Nuhu posted seven rebounds and six blocks. Cal Hansen had 21 points for the Loggers. Walker Shibley-Styer added 12 points and Jourdan Joseph scored 11. Portland State faces Indiana on the road on Saturday. The game was an exhibition for D-III Puget Sound. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
